---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Pricing â€” ShotAPI"
  description="Simple, affordable pricing. Free tier with 100 screenshots/day. Paid plans from $9/mo."
  path="/pricing"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <div class="mb-12 text-center">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground">
        Simple, Transparent Pricing
      </h1>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-muted-foreground">
        No hidden fees. No per-screenshot charges on paid plans. Just a flat
        monthly rate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Pricing cards -->
    <div class="mb-16 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- Free -->
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Free</h3>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">For trying things out</p>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">$0</span>
          <span class="text-muted-foreground">/month</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="mb-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            100 screenshots/day
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            All formats (PNG, JPEG, WebP, PDF)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Full page capture
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Dark mode support
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Custom viewport
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-muted-foreground/40">&#10007;</span>
            <span class="text-muted-foreground">Priority support</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a
          href="/keys"
          class="block rounded-md border border-border bg-secondary py-3 text-center text-sm font-medium text-secondary-foreground transition hover:bg-secondary/80"
          >Get Free Key</a
        >
      </div>

      <!-- Starter -->
      <div
        class="relative rounded-lg border-2 border-foreground bg-card p-6"
      >
        <div
          class="absolute -top-3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-foreground px-3 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-background"
        >
          POPULAR
        </div>
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Starter</h3>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          For side projects & MVPs
        </p>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">$9</span>
          <span class="text-muted-foreground">/month</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="mb-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            <strong>2,500</strong> screenshots/day
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            All formats (PNG, JPEG, WebP, PDF)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Full page capture
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Dark mode support
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Custom viewport
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Email support
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a
          href="/keys"
          class="block rounded-md bg-primary py-3 text-center text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground transition hover:bg-primary/90"
          >Get Started</a
        >
      </div>

      <!-- Pro -->
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-6">
        <h3 class="mb-1 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Pro</h3>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">For production apps</p>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">$29</span>
          <span class="text-muted-foreground">/month</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="mb-6 space-y-3 text-sm text-foreground/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            <strong>10,000</strong> screenshots/day
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            All formats (PNG, JPEG, WebP, PDF)
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Full page capture
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Dark mode support
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Custom viewport
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-emerald-500">&#10003;</span>
            Priority support
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a
          href="/keys"
          class="block rounded-md border border-border bg-secondary py-3 text-center text-sm font-medium text-secondary-foreground transition hover:bg-secondary/80"
          >Get Started</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-center text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">
        Pricing FAQ
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <details class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card">
          <summary
            class="cursor-pointer p-4 font-medium text-foreground transition hover:text-muted-foreground"
          >
            What happens if I hit my daily limit?
          </summary>
          <p class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            You'll receive a 429 response with a message indicating when your
            limit resets (midnight UTC). Your API key continues to work the next
            day.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card">
          <summary
            class="cursor-pointer p-4 font-medium text-foreground transition hover:text-muted-foreground"
          >
            Can I upgrade or downgrade anytime?
          </summary>
          <p class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Yes. Changes take effect immediately. If you downgrade, you keep the
            higher limit until the end of your current billing period.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card">
          <summary
            class="cursor-pointer p-4 font-medium text-foreground transition hover:text-muted-foreground"
          >
            Is there a per-screenshot charge?
          </summary>
          <p class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            No. Paid plans include a fixed daily limit with no per-screenshot
            fees. Use as many as your plan allows each day.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card">
          <summary
            class="cursor-pointer p-4 font-medium text-foreground transition hover:text-muted-foreground"
          >
            Do you offer annual billing?
          </summary>
          <p class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Not yet, but we're considering it. All plans are currently
            month-to-month with no commitment.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
